          "text": "I have a clear picture. The user asked about configuring DEFAULT_API_BASE_URL. The codebase supports multiple ways to configure the API base URL with the following precedence:\n\n- Config file `api_base_url` setting\n- `GIT_AI_API_BASE_URL` environment variable\n- `DEFAULT_API_BASE_URL` compile-time constant\n\nThe configuration follows this order of preference: file config takes priority over environment variables, which in turn take priority over the default value. For clients using the git-ai CLI, configure the backend URL by setting either:\n- `GIT_AI_API_BASE_URL` environment variable\n- `api_base_url` in `~/.git-ai/config.json`\n\nThis applies when the client points to a self-hosted backend like Railway. For Railway deployment of the backend, the user needs to understand that the Rust client doesn't require changes for arbitrary deployments. Instead, they should:\n\n- Use `GIT_AI_API_BASE_URL` environment variable when running git-ai\n- Or set `api_base_url` in the config file\n\nFor Railway specifically:\n- Add `GIT_AI_API_BASE_URL` variable in Railway's dashboard under Variables tab\n- Note that Railway environment variables apply to the deployed service itself, not the client-side tool\n\nNo changes needed in the Rust codebase for this scenario.",
