        {
          "type": "thinking",
          "text": "Now I understand the full picture:\n\n- 1. CAS upload is gated by `client.is_logged_in() || using_custom_api`.  \n`using_custom_api` is true when `config.api_base_url()` is not equal to `DEFAULT_API_BASE_URL`, meaning custom API URLs (like `GIT_AI_API_BASE_URL`) enable uploads even without login.  \n\nUpload behavior:\n- Default URL + logged in  upload\n- Custom URL + not logged in  upload (via `using_custom_api`)\n- Default URL + not logged in  no upload So the user's understanding is mostly correct.  \n\nThe issue arises because the server URL changes on redeployment, causing problems with the current design:\n- `DEFAULT_API_BASE_URL` is set at compile time, so old clients may still reference outdated domains via embedded defaults or stored `messages_url` in commits.\n- CAS uses content-addressed hashes, meaning the actual content remains accessible if the server domain changes, provided there's proper redirection or aliasing in place.",
          "timestamp": "2026-05-03T06:39:48.473Z",
          "id": "515ff864-db48-441c-a41d-2d033f1533ee"
        },
        {
          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "Here’s a concise picture of **what the code does today** and a **reasonable design direction** for “always ours” + moving hosts.\n\n### What happens today\n\nIn `post_commit`, CAS enqueue runs only when the user **is logged in** or **`api_base_url` is not equal to** the baked-in `DEFAULT_API_BASE_URL` (“custom API” heuristic):\n\n```339:389:src/authorship/post_commit.rs\n    let (effective_storage, using_custom_api, custom_attrs) = (\n        config.effective_prompt_storage(&Some(repo.clone())),\n        config.api_base_url() != crate::config::DEFAULT_API_BASE_URL,\n        ...\n    );\n    ...\n            let should_enqueue_cas =\n                client.is_logged_in() || using_custom_api;\n```\n\nUploaded blobs get URLs like `{current api_base_url}/cas/{hash}`, so whatever base URL is configured at commit time gets **frozen into history** on that commit path.\n\nSo: uploads are **not** “magic always to our infra”; they’re gated by auth or by “not exactly the shipped default URL.” Changing only your Railway default domain doesn’t by itself fix “always upload” or “URLs never stale.”\n\n### Design recommendation (layers)\n\n**1. Operations: one stable hostname (best ROI)**  \nPut the API behind a **name you control** (custom domain → Railway, or a CDN/proxy). Redeploys then change **underlying** infra, not the string every client and every old `messages_url` uses. This is the standard fix for “Railway URL changed.”\n\n**2. Compatibility: redirects or shared blob store**  \nOld commits already store full `…/cas/{hash}` URLs. If the host changes anyway:\n\n- **Same CAS backend**, new hostname → **301/302** old host → new host on `/cas/*`, or\n- Same bucket/storage with both hosts → URLs keep working once DNS cutover + TLS are right.\n\nIf each redeploy is a **new** empty store without migration, old hashes are genuinely broken regardless of client design.\n\n**3. Product/config: explicit “always upload to configured API”**  \nIf “always ours” is a policy decision, encode it explicitly (e.g. config flag / tier), instead of **`logged_in || url != compile_time_default`**, which breaks when:\n\n- Default URL in binaries is updated, or  \n- Prod URL intentionally matches default but you still want uploads without tying to login quirks.\n\n Tie uploads to **`api_base_url`** (plus auth if required by your API), not to “did they override the magic constant?”\n\n**4. Don’t rely on bouncing `DEFAULT_*` every redeploy**  \nClients ship at different versions; `.env`-only Railway vars don’t rewrite URLs already embedded in commits. Stability is naming + redirects + storage continuity, not “we changed the env default again.”\n\n**Summary:** Use a **stable public API hostname**, keep **CAS storage continuity** across deploys (or redirects), and add an **explicit client policy** for “always enqueue CAS to `api_base_url`” plus auth tokens as your server requires. That combination matches “always upload to our server” and survives redeploys much better than retuning `DEFAULT_API_BASE_URL` alone.",
